03:11.858 --> 03:13.443
NOW WHAT, HUH?

03:13.526 --> 03:16.154
BOY, ARE YOU GOING
TO GET IT NOW.

03:16.237 --> 03:19.115
(<i> echoing</i> ):
HEY, HEY, HEY, HEY...

03:19.198 --> 03:22.619
SOMEBODY'S GOING
TO PAY FOR THAT GLASS.

03:22.702 --> 03:24.621
(<i> applause</i> )

03:24.704 --> 03:27.707
WE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

03:29.042 --> 03:33.922
{\an5}Pig Announcer:
<i>THE FATHEADS</i> IS SPONSORED
BY PUPPY NUGGETS.

03:34.005 --> 03:35.214
They're little things

03:35.298 --> 03:37.050
and you're just going to go nuts
over them.

03:37.133 --> 03:41.137
{\an1}<i>THE FATHEADS,</i> CREATED
BY RALPH BIGHEAD.

03:41.220 --> 03:42.472
Together:
RALPH BIGHEAD?

03:42.555 --> 03:43.806
OH...

03:43.890 --> 03:45.808
DO YOU THINK...

03:47.018 --> 03:51.356
(<i> screaming and crying</i> )

03:51.439 --> 03:55.735
OH, HOW CAN OUR BABY
SEE US THIS WAY?

03:55.818 --> 03:56.653
BABY?

03:56.736 --> 04:00.114
{\an1}THAT BABY HUMILIATES US
WEEK AFTER WEEK

04:00.198 --> 04:01.115
ON NATIONAL TELEVISION.

04:01.199 --> 04:03.785
MAKES US LOOK LIKE
A COUPLE OF FROGS.

04:03.868 --> 04:06.371
I... NEVER...

04:06.454 --> 04:07.080
{\an1}WANT TO...

04:07.163 --> 04:11.084
HEAR THE NAME
RALPH BIGHEAD

04:11.167 --> 04:13.378
AGAIN!

04:14.462 --> 04:16.172
(<i> doorbell rings</i> )

04:16.255 --> 04:17.798
I'LL GET IT.

04:20.259 --> 04:22.220
ARE YOU RELATED
TO RALPH BIGHEAD?

04:23.304 --> 04:26.766
{\an1}UH, BECAUSE I'M A BIG,
BIG FAN OF <i> MEET THE FATHEADS</i>

04:26.849 --> 04:28.559
AND I THOUGH MAYBE HE

04:28.643 --> 04:30.395
WAS YOUR NEPHEW, OR YOUR SON.

04:30.478 --> 04:30.853
SON?

04:30.937 --> 04:36.150
I HAVE NO SON!

04:38.277 --> 04:41.197
ROCKO, I MUST
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

04:41.281 --> 04:41.906
UM...

04:41.990 --> 04:46.369
RALPH BIGHEAD IS OUR ONLY SON.

04:46.452 --> 04:50.915
{\an1}HERE HE IS AT THE BEGINNING
OF HIS LIFE CYCLE.

04:50.999 --> 04:55.503
OH, JUST LOOK
AT THAT LITTLE TAIL.

04:55.586 --> 04:59.590
HE WAS SUCH A CUTE TADPOLE.

04:59.674 --> 05:02.552
(<i> sobbing</i> )

05:02.635 --> 05:03.720
(<i> blowing nose</i> )

05:03.803 --> 05:05.972
OH...

05:06.055 --> 05:09.976
LITTLE RALPHIE SHOWED AN
EARLY TALENT IN THE ARTS

05:10.059 --> 05:13.730
AND WANTED TO GROW UP
TO BE A GREAT PAINTER.

05:13.813 --> 05:15.064
ED HAD HOPES THAT ONE DAY

05:15.148 --> 05:19.235
RALPH WOULD JOIN HIM
AS AN EXECUTIVE

05:19.318 --> 05:22.530
AT THE CONGLOM-O CORPORATION.

05:22.613 --> 05:25.908
AND WHEN THAT DAY
FINALLY CAME

05:25.992 --> 05:29.912
ED WAS BURSTING
WITH FATHERLY PRIDE.

05:29.996 --> 05:31.748
BUT, BUT SOMETHING...

05:31.831 --> 05:35.209
WENT TERRIBLY...

05:35.293 --> 05:37.211
(<i> sobbing</i> )

05:37.295 --> 05:38.254
WHAT HAPPENED?

05:38.337 --> 05:43.468
COME TO THINK OF IT,
I DON'T KNOW.

05:43.551 --> 05:46.304
(<i> sobbing loudly</i> )

05:46.387 --> 05:48.473
OH, MY BABY...

05:49.474 --> 05:53.770
{\an1}GEE, MRS. BIGHEAD, I WISH
I COULD HELP, BUT...

05:53.853 --> 05:56.314
OH, OH, ROCKO, ROCKO, DARLING

05:56.397 --> 05:59.942
WOULD YOU BRING
MY LITTLE RALPHIE HOME?

06:00.026 --> 06:01.110
{\an1}UM...

06:01.194 --> 06:04.489
{\an1}IT'S OUR 30th ANNIVERSARY
NEXT WEEKEND.

06:04.572 --> 06:07.450
IT WOULD MEAN SO MUCH TO US.

06:07.533 --> 06:10.369
