{\an1}GET THIS FLYING
DISEASE OFF MY HEAD!

14:26.532 --> 14:28.033
(<i> applause</i> )

14:39.295 --> 14:40.754
(<i> winding</i> )

14:40.838 --> 14:42.131
(<i> squeaking</i> )

14:42.214 --> 14:44.300
Ed:
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN

14:44.383 --> 14:47.136
FELLOW CONGLOM-O EMPLOYEES

14:47.219 --> 14:51.473
{\an1}IT GIVES ME GREAT PLEASURE
TO BEGIN THE FISCAL YEAR

14:51.557 --> 14:56.353
{\an1}WITH THE INCLUSION OF
A NEW EMPLOYEE AT CONGLOM-O.

14:56.437 --> 14:59.565
MY SON, RALPH.

15:01.817 --> 15:05.237
AND NOW, WITHOUT
FURTHER A-DOO-DOO...

15:05.321 --> 15:06.614
(<i> fanfare</i> )

15:06.697 --> 15:08.157
...THE DONUT.

15:08.240 --> 15:11.076
All:
OOH...

15:11.160 --> 15:13.579
ITS CIRCULAR SHAPE SYMBOLIZING

15:13.662 --> 15:17.666
CONGLOM-O'S RELENTLESS PURSUIT
OF THE ALMIGHTY DOLLAR.

15:17.750 --> 15:21.795
I NOW CALL UPON MY SON
TO CARRY OUT THE NOBLE TRADITION

15:21.879 --> 15:25.382
ESTABLISHED BY
OUR FOUNDING FATHERS

15:25.466 --> 15:28.636
{\an1}OF BREAKING
THIS GOLDEN RING OF DOUGH

15:28.719 --> 15:33.891
THEREBY ISSUING IN
THE NEW FISCAL YEAR.

15:36.018 --> 15:38.103
SON, MAKE ME PROUD.

15:41.607 --> 15:43.609
HE'S NOT BREAKING THE DONUT.

15:43.692 --> 15:46.195
FAMINE AND PESTILENCE
WILL BEFALL US.

15:47.321 --> 15:49.948
BUT, DAD, I CAN'T.

15:50.032 --> 15:50.491
(<i> crowd gasps</i> )

15:50.574 --> 15:52.701
Man:
WE'RE DOOMED!

15:52.785 --> 15:54.203
DON'T START WITH ME.

15:54.286 --> 15:55.788
BREAK THE DONUT.

15:55.871 --> 15:58.540
FOR THE LAST TIME,
BREAK THE DONUT.

15:58.624 --> 16:01.126
(<i> crowd moans</i> )

16:06.840 --> 16:08.967
(<i> cheering</i> )

16:09.051 --> 16:10.386
SPEECH! SPEECH!

16:10.469 --> 16:12.388
(<i> burping</i> )

16:12.471 --> 16:13.555
UM...

16:13.639 --> 16:14.932
(<i> microphone squeals</i> )

16:15.015 --> 16:16.725
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN, I...

16:16.809 --> 16:19.103
I DON'T WANT
TO WORK AT CONGLOM-O.

16:19.186 --> 16:20.979
(<i> gasping</i> )

16:21.063 --> 16:22.523
IN FACT, I'M MOVING...

16:22.606 --> 16:23.732
TO HOLLOWOOD.

16:25.818 --> 16:27.319
TO BECOME A...

16:27.403 --> 16:28.696
CARTOONIST.

16:28.779 --> 16:30.864
(<i> screaming</i> )

16:37.788 --> 16:38.706
EXCUSE ME,
MR. BIGHEAD

16:38.789 --> 16:41.250
{\an1}DID I GET
THIS RIGHT?

16:41.333 --> 16:42.376
{\an1}YOUR SON WILL
BE MOVING TO...

16:42.459 --> 16:47.923
I HAVE NO SON!

16:48.006 --> 16:50.426
(<i> sighing</i> )

16:50.509 --> 16:51.844
(<i> clanking shut</i> )

16:51.927 --> 16:53.971
{\an5}Man:
A ONE, A TWO, A ONE,
TWO, THREE, FOUR...

16:54.054 --> 16:57.516
(<i> big band music starting up</i> )

16:57.599 --> 16:59.727
(<i> fly buzzing</i> )

17:23.834 --> 17:28.047
MRS. BIGHEAD, WHERE ARE YOU?

17:30.215 --> 17:31.258
AH-HA.

17:36.472 --> 17:37.514
IS THAT YOU, ROSIE?

17:37.598 --> 17:40.642
I KNOW IT'S YOU

17:40.726 --> 17:43.729
{\an1}'CAUSE I CAN SMELL
YOUR SUCCOTASH.

17:43.812 --> 17:46.982
(<i> giggling nervously</i> )

17:48.692 --> 17:51.737
LET'S DANCE.

18:09.463 --> 18:11.882
ROCKO?

18:11.965 --> 18:14.218
MRS. BIGHEAD, IT'S YOU.

18:14.301 --> 18:16.929
{\an1}LISTEN, I FOUND
RALPH, BUT--

18:17.012 --> 18:20.098
MY RALPH
IS HERE AT LAST.

18:20.182 --> 18:24.102
NO, WAIT, MRS. BIGHEAD...

18:24.186 --> 18:26.980
OH, MY POOR, POOR, LOST SON.

18:27.064 --> 18:28.774
HE'S HERE.

18:31.276 --> 18:33.320
MRS. BIGHEAD,
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND...

18:36.615 --> 18:40.244
OH, HE MUST BE SO HANDSOME.

18:45.040 --> 18:47.167
I'M SO EXCITED.

18:47.251 --> 18:48.210
(<i> glass breaking</i> )

18:55.843 --> 18:57.135
ATTENTION, EVERYONE.

18:57.219 --> 18:59.096
I'D LIKE TO
MAKE A TOAST

18:59.179 --> 19:03.559
TO MY LOVELY TOAD
OF A WIFE, BEV.

19:03.642 --> 19:06.061
I REMEMBER THE DAY WE MET

19:06.144 --> 19:09.439
{\an1}OUR TONGUES TANGLED
AROUND THE SAME FLY CARCASS.

19:09.523 --> 19:12.234
{\an1}OH, ED.

19:12.317 --> 19:14.987
THROUGH 30 YEARS OF MARRIAGE

19:15.070 --> 19:16.238
WE HAVE A SINGLE REGRET...

19:19.449 --> 19:20.742
YOU!

19:20.826 --> 19:23.078
(<i> crowd gasping</i> )

19:23.161 --> 19:24.746
RALPHIE, DARLING!

19:24.830 --> 19:27.916
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

19:28.000 --> 19:31.044
{\an1}THIS
LITTLE BEAVER CAME TO HOLLOWOOD

19:31.128 --> 19:32.754
AND SAID YOU WANTED ME HERE.

19:32.838 --> 19:33.839
WANTED YOU?!

19:33.922 --> 19:37.426
AFTER THE WAY YOU'VE DISGRACED
THE BIGHEAD NAME?

19:37.509 --> 19:39.386
HA! GO BACK TO HOLLOWOOD

19:39.469 --> 19:40.721
AND, THAT, THAT...

19:40.804 --> 19:44.182
THAT CARTOON OF YOURS.

19:44.266 --> 19:45.601
CARTOONS ARE MY LIFE

19:45.684 --> 19:47.227
AND I THOUGHT THAT MAYBE

19:47.311 --> 19:49.938
{\an1}YOU HAD FINALLY
COME TO RESPECT THAT.

19:50.022 --> 19:53.150
RESPECT? WHAT DO
YOU KNOW ABOUT RESPECT?

19:53.233 --> 19:55.777
REMEMBER CONGLOM-O?

19:55.861 --> 19:56.904
CONGLOM-O?

19:56.987 --> 19:58.739
(<i> arguing</i> )

19:58.822 --> 20:01.867
STOP IT! STOP IT! STOP IT!

20:01.950 --> 20:05.996
OH, LET'S JUST
BE A FAMILY AGAIN.

20:06.079 --> 20:10.208
OVER MY DEAD BODY.

20:10.292 --> 20:12.461
HAVE IT YOUR WAY, DAD.

20:12.544 --> 20:15.797
(<i> crowd screaming</i> )

20:15.881 --> 20:16.965
(<i> gasps</i> )

20:24.890 --> 20:29.394
(<i> fly buzzing</i> )

20:29.478 --> 20:31.521
YOU, YOU, YOU KEPT IT.

20:31.605 --> 20:33.482
YOU...

20:33.565 --> 20:35.400
(<i> sobbing</i> ):
MY BOY.

20:36.693 --> 20:38.403
SON!

20:40.405 --> 20:42.199
(<i> jingling</i> )

20:46.328 --> 20:46.411
AH...

20:49.206 --> 20:51.416
THE DONUT,
YOU KEPT IT.

20:51.500 --> 20:55.671
YOU DO CARE
ABOUT CONGLOM-O.

20:55.754 --> 20:59.007
NO, I DON'T CARE
ABOUT CONGLOM-O.

20:59.091 --> 21:00.842
I CARE ABOUT...

21:00.926 --> 21:02.344
{\an1}YOU.

21:02.427 --> 21:02.636
{\an3}SON!

21:02.719 --> 21:05.555
{\an1}DAD!

21:05.639 --> 21:07.849
Crowd:
AW...

21:07.933 --> 21:10.394
MY SON.

21:10.477 --> 21:10.727
MAKE A LOT OF MONEY?

21:10.811 --> 21:13.730
{\an1}OH, DAD.

21:13.814 --> 21:15.899
HA! THAT'S MY BOY.

21:15.983 --> 21:17.693
(<i> crowd cheering</i> )

21:17.776 --> 21:22.197
OH, MY BOYS, MY BOYS.

21:22.280 --> 21:26.368
UNCLE ED, CAN WE
BREAK THE PINATA NOW?

21:26.451 --> 21:27.494
Ed:
PINATA? SURE.

21:27.577 --> 21:29.663
(<i> gulping</i> )

21:31.498 --> 21:33.875
{\an5}Announcer:
HEY, KIDS, STAY TUNED
FOR THE SEASON PREMIERE

21:33.959 --> 21:36.003
OF <i> MEET THE FATHEADS.</i>

21:36.086 --> 21:38.338
I WONDER WHAT KIND OF TROUBLE

21:38.422 --> 21:40.465
THEY'LL GET INTO THIS YEAR.

21:40.549 --> 21:43.051
(<i> blowing raspberries</i> )

21:43.135 --> 21:45.137
QUIET, YOU TWO,
IT'S STARTING.

21:45.220 --> 21:47.222
{\an1}OH, DON'T
MIND HIM, BOYS.

21:47.305 --> 21:50.892
{\an1}WE'RE JUST SO EXCITED
TO HAVE OUR SONNY-BOY BACK.

21:50.976 --> 21:53.020
I CANNOT THANK YOU ENOUGH.

21:53.103 --> 21:55.897
{\an1}IT MUST HAVE
BEEN VERY DIFFICULT.

21:55.981 --> 21:58.358
WELL, ACTUALLY,
IT'S QUITE A STORY.

21:58.442 --> 21:59.401
YOU SEE...

21:59.484 --> 22:01.278
QUIET, DEAR, IT'S STARTING.

22:02.863 --> 22:05.073
{\an1}THAT'S IT.

22:05.157 --> 22:05.991
THE BAKE SALE IS OFF.

22:06.074 --> 22:08.702
(<i> audience applauding</i> )

22:08.785 --> 22:11.580
(<i> laughing</i> )

22:11.663 --> 22:14.583
OH, GREAT, HERE COMES THAT
DISGUSTING NEIGHBOR OF OURS

22:14.666 --> 22:17.878
{\an3}ROLO.

22:21.840 --> 22:24.259
OH, HELLO, ROLO,
WON'T YOU COME IN?

22:24.342 --> 22:25.093
YES, THANK YOU, MATE.

22:25.177 --> 22:29.097
WOULD YOU LIKE
SOME CHEESECAKE, ROLO?

22:29.181 --> 22:31.683
DON'T GIVE HIM ANYTHING!

22:31.767 --> 22:34.144
{\an1}WHY, THANK YOU,
I'D LOVE SOME, MATE.

22:37.606 --> 22:38.440
THANK YOU.

22:38.523 --> 22:40.400
IT WAS DELICIOUS, MATE.

22:43.695 --> 22:45.864
PINEAPPLES!

22:47.866 --> 22:51.286
OH, BOY, WHEN ARE WE GOING
TO HAVE PINEAPPLES, MATE?

22:51.369 --> 22:52.704
(<i> laughing</i> )

22:52.788 --> 22:54.498
GOOD NIGHT, HOSERS.

23:06.551 --> 23:07.886
HEY.

23:07.969 --> 23:08.929
I DON'T GET IT.

23:09.012 --> 23:10.347
(<i> man laughing</i> )

